Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

The idea is to selectively enable or disable the following behavior:

  If a file has SOM_FL_STRICT then return ms_size and ms_blocks as authoritative to the client (by setting OBD_MD_FLSIZE | OBD_MD_FLBLOCKS in the response body).

But this does more than that and has follow on effects in mdt_lsom_donwgrade() and other places.

Rather than changing mdt_get_som(), I think it's enough (and better) to just change the behavior in the info->mti_som_valid branch of mdt_pack_attr2body().


    } else if (info->mti_som_valid) { /* som is valid */
         b->mbo_valid |= OBD_MD_FLSIZE | OBD_MD_FLBLOCKS;
    }

It would be good while we're here to change mti_som_valid to mti_som_is_strict.
